The paper deals with channel state information (CSI) feedback and cooperative recovery in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed framework also involves deep learning techniques (cs.LG) and system and control theory (cs.SY) to reduce feedback overhead and improve performance. Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of multiple antennas in UE, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
